Rating: 4
This is a good recipe, and is a much appreciated vegetarian-friendly version of french onion soup. It is not exactly like the original, but it is close enough to kill my cravings. Reducing the broth and slowly carmelizing the onions really makes a difference in the flavor, but it takes a long time to do. In my experience, it is very necessary to take the time to do this soup properly instead of rushing through it. The "quicker" ways of making this soup yield a bland and watery soup. Also, I liked having gruyere croutons better than goat cheese for this soup.

