Rating: 4
Excellent -- perhaps even superior -- variation on French Onion Soup. I used rum rather than brandy and substituted red wine for white with great results (red wine has more depth (and health benefits) than white). As others have mentioned, the broth is a bit thin. A nice solution is to purée 1/3 of the soup at the end of the cooking process, which will thicken the broth and deepen the flavor without losing the chunkier textures which are essential to the character of the soup. Also, I would suggest sautéing the baguette slices in garlic and olive oil until browned rather than merely toasting them.

